# SignalPilot Core Rules

## Architecture
- All data models are in `src/signalpilot/models.py` (pydantic v2)
- `Evidence = Annotated[Union[Signal, LogCluster, GitChange], Field(discriminator="type")]` — always use discriminated union
- Collectors are in `src/signalpilot/collectors/` — all implement `BaseCollector` with `is_available()` + `collect()`
- RCA rules are pure functions in `rca/rules.py` with signature `rule_fn(ctx: RcaContext) -> list[Finding]`
- The engine in `rca/engine.py` wraps every rule in try/except — rules must never crash the engine
- `get_settings()` is `@lru_cache(maxsize=1)` — call `.cache_clear()` in tests using `monkeypatch.setenv`

## Python conventions
- Python 3.12+, strict typing everywhere
- Pydantic v2: use `model_copy(update={...})` not `.copy()`
- Use `from __future__ import annotations` for forward refs
- `Signal.type = "signal"` (discriminator), never omit
- All collectors handle exceptions gracefully and return `[]` on failure
- `redact_secrets()` must be applied to all log text before storage

## Testing
- Unit tests use JSON fixtures in `tests/fixtures/k8s/` — no live cluster
- E2E tests in `tests/e2e/` skip automatically if no cluster available
- Signal fixtures always include `type="signal"` field
- Use `freezegun` for time-sensitive tests

## K8s compatibility
- Target K3s v1.22+ (rancher-desktop)
- Use `core/v1` events API (not `events.k8s.io/v1`)
- Crashloop detection: check BOTH `state.waiting.reason == "CrashLoopBackOff"` AND `restart_count >= 3` with `last_state.terminated.reason != OOMKilled` (pod briefly re-runs between crashes)
- Metrics-server: use `CustomObjectsApi` for `apis/metrics.k8s.io/v1beta1`

## File structure
- `src/signalpilot/` — source package (src layout)
- `tests/unit/` — fast fixture-based unit tests
- `tests/e2e/` — live cluster E2E tests
- `tests/fixtures/k8s/` — recorded K8s API JSON responses
- `deploy/samples/` — scenario manifests for `signalpilot-test` namespace
- `scripts/` — setup_test.sh, run_e2e.sh
- `.signalpilot/` — runtime data dir (analyses, timelines, verifications)
